<br>
<!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i>  In one of the many universe, there exist a line of mages who can use the ancient magic of Art. By harnessing their artistic skills to ensorceled pencils and pens, they can call forth creatures from their minds to do their bidding. Some give the world heros and legends, some bring into the world hideous evils. Their powers are growing, and the quest has begun.</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--><br>
<br>
Basically, this is a card game that resembles Magic: the Gathering, my favorite card game. You make up a deck of cards and use them to destroy your opponent. There are at least three different kinds of cards:<br>
<br>
Artist cards<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE IMAGE START--><img src="http://mylakovich.homestead.com/files/pics/jpeg/Cards/mylak.jpg"><!--EZCODE IMAGE END--><br>
<br>
These cards represent an Art Mage, or someone who can use the Art magic of character summoning.<br>
<br>
Character cards<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE IMAGE START--><img src="http://mylakovich.homestead.com/files/pics/jpeg/Cards/westernmacarthur.jpg"><!--EZCODE IMAGE END--><br>
<br>
These cards represent a Character, or a person or thing summoned using the Art Magic.<br>
<br>
Action Cards<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE IMAGE START--><img src="http://mylakovich.homestead.com/files/pics/jpeg/Cards/inksketch.jpg"><!--EZCODE IMAGE END--><br>
<br>
These cards represent magical actions that involve Art Magic, but do not summon characters.<br>
<br>
There will be more card types coming soon!<br>
<br>
Basically, you use character cards to supply yourself with points, represented by the Pencil, Pen, and Mouse symbols. This represents the Magic ability that the artist possesed in the areas of scetching, inking, and CG. Artists also have an ability that can be played for the effect labeled on the card. you must pay the points and if ther is a symbol that reads TAP, you must tap that artist, meaning turn it on its side. This allows you to do the ability only one a turn.<br>
<br>
The characters have a creation cost, located in the top of their text box. This is the required skill points needed from one of your artists to play that character. The character's vital information is given in the box to the right, as well as their Chart. The chart has their attack power in red, defence power in blue, magic or quickness in orange, and magic resistance or reflex in teal. When in combat, the characters deal damage equal to their attack power to oppposing characters or players. They also deal damage equal to their magic or quickness. if a character block an attacking character, they deal damage to each other. A character is destroyed if they are dealt red damage greater than or equal to their defence, and orange damage equal to or greater than their reflex on the same turn.<br>
<br>
Characters also have an ability in their left side of the box.<br>
<br>
Ability cards have an effect that happens when they are cast. The effect does what is writen on the card, then goes into the discard pile. They can do anything from make you draw cards, to change the stats of your characters, or destroy certain cards in play, or any variety of effects.<br>
<br>
Coming soon: &quot;enchantment&quot; like cards that stay in play and provide a constant ability or effect.<br>
<br>
Tool cards that have useful abilities when combined with with artists or characters.<br>
<br>
The coolest thing about this opportunity is that as an ongoing submission based event, you can submit your ideas and I will make them into cards. Once There are enough of a variety, People can use them in matches against each other.<br>
<br>
If you want yourself or your characters to appear on cards, send me an e-mail to mcgrewwj@aol.com with the following:<br>
<br>
Your desired screen name-<br>
Information that describes you or your art style. this will be used to determine what ability your card will have<br>
some links or examples of your artwork. this will determine the number of points your character will provide.<br>
a desired quote. something that describes your personality, use good judgement when thinking of a quote. if I don't like it, i will invent my own instead.<br>
and finally a self portrait. this will appear as the illustration on your card. try to make it the very best you can do, because this will be seen by everyone and helps to justify the points your artists and characters get.<br>
<br>
for characters, describe the characters personality, fighting style, strengths and weaknesses, and what element you think the character should have. Also include a good picture of the character, and a quote that helps the reader understanmd your character or is entertaining. Keep in mind that your character cannot cost more than the points that your artist card provides. Characters with high attack and defence tend to have bad effects or cost more, and likewise characters with good effects or abilities tend to lack in offence or defence or have a high cost.<br>
<br>
you can also submit ideas for ability cards. just describe the ability as best you can, and also a picture and flavor text would be helpful.<br>
<br>
Well, I hope everyone is as excited as I am about this! My goal is to have a lot of artist and character cards from everybody on Polykarbon, so even if you don't know me personally, or you just got here, or whatever, submit yourself to the cards! if everybody contributes, we should have a lot!<br>
<br>
To get your creative juices flowing, here are all the cards I have done already! Feel free to comment on them!<br>
<br>
