<br>
You supply the ideas, I make the cards. I have the PSD templates all done, you you just email me the idea, and i will put everything in card form. There is no work on your part, unless you want to have your own quote on the card.<br>
<br>
And to answer Traum4's question, the idea is to take any character that you like and make a card of it. Old characters are perfectly fine. Thats one of the main draws is that older characters have moves or personalities that people have already seen in previous fight clubs, and they can see it in card for. So yes, any character is perfectly fine.<br>
<br>
To those who think this might be a hassle, I will accomidate you, so don't think this will be a time investment. All you have to do is write maybe a few sentances describing your character, and have a picture of it. I will do all the work, and post the finished version, after i approve it with you. I think some people thought that they would have to draw up the cards, but don't worry, I will handle the nitty gritty.<br>
<br>
I hope now the confusion is lifted and people will see this as a fun opportunity!<br>
<br>
